</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792159FFF4FF221F59FB85FAAA" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22159FFF4FF221F59FB85FAAA" blockId="11.[151,1437,1116,2043]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF221F59FE8FFB92" bold="true" box="[151,273,1116,1142]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF221F59FE94FB92" bold="true" box="[151,266,1116,1142]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B172159FFF4FEC71F59FE44FB93" box="[370,474,1116,1143]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.47" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="14.7">14.7 mm</quantity>
. Width 
<quantity id="4CF09B172159FFF4FD861F59FD10FB93" box="[563,654,1116,1143]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
. Dorsally dark yellow. Beneath uniformly yellow (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FB641F59FAD3FB92" box="[1233,1357,1116,1142]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 1K–L</figureCitation>
). Head with a rectangular, small, median, punctured, black maculae between ocelli (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FC5A1F85FBD6FB7E" box="[1007,1096,1152,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
). Pronotal disc with punctures brown; posterior margin with a band of black punctures. Scutellum with black punctures on black spots forming a few irregular lines (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FEF01FCDFE01FB06" box="[325,415,1224,1250]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
). Humeral angles projection short, dentiform. Costal margin of corium densely punctured, punctures small and brown (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FE7A1FE9FDB9FAE2" box="[463,551,1260,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
); hypocostal ridge with few, black, small punctures on spots. Beneath uniformly and densely punctured, except on median line; punctures brown to black, most on black spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FB001E15FA94FACE" box="[1205,1290,1296,1322]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 1L</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim of the pygophore deeply excavated, almost as excavated as dorsal rim (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FC011E31FB90FAAA" box="[948,1038,1332,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[154,1417,400,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-91@12.[154,1434,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia of G. stichtocephala sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500689/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792159FFF4FF721E5DFB40F8A3" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22159FFF4FF721E5DFD9CF9C2" blockId="11.[151,1437,1116,2043]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721E5DFECAFA96" bold="true" box="[199,340,1368,1394]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721E5DFED3FA96" bold="true" box="[199,333,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head wider than long (1.4 times). Antennal segments I–III and base of fourth spotted. Thorax: Pronotum wider than long (3.4 times); cicatrices delimited by punctures, weakly punctuated. Evaporatorium slightly darker than pleura, densely punctured, dull, and slightly shagreen; lateral areas oval and punctured (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FADA1EA5FF26FA3A" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 1L</figureCitation>
). Metasternal process yellow; anterior bifurcation with arms strongly acuminate; with few spots posteriorly. Legs not spotted (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FE921EEDFEE0F9E6" box="[295,382,1512,1538]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 1L</figureCitation>
). Abdomen: connexivum with punctures shallow; segments III–VI with medial callus. Both trichobothria lateral to spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F22159FFF4FF721D2AFB40F8A3" blockId="11.[151,1437,1116,2043]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721D2AFE9CF9AE" bold="true" box="[199,258,1583,1610]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FEA41D35FECBF9AF" box="[273,341,1584,1611]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[154,1417,400,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-91@12.[154,1434,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia of G. stichtocephala sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500689/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Pygophore dark yellow, subtrapezoidal (1.1 times), dorsal rim slightly projected over the genital cup. Posterolateral angles strongly developed (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FD131D51FC9FF98A" box="[678,769,1620,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[154,1417,400,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-91@12.[154,1434,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia of G. stichtocephala sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500689/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
), shallowly concave, inner part outlined by a stripe of dark brown punctures. Superior processes of the genital cup large, subtriangular, touching the dorsal rim of the genital cup. Parameres with anterior lobe rounded, posterior lobe small and dentiform connected with a long black carina (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FF151DC5FF62F93E" box="[160,252,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[154,1417,400,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-91@12.[154,1434,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia of G. stichtocephala sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500689/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger yellow, elongated (1.5 times); slightly constricted laterally; carina of the posterior surface restricted to basal half (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FE2A1DE1FE66F91A" box="[415,504,1764,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[154,1417,400,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-91@12.[154,1434,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia of G. stichtocephala sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500689/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim strongly excavated, widely opened, almost level with dorsal rim (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FADA1DE1FF41F8C6" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[154,1417,400,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-91@12.[154,1434,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia of G. stichtocephala sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500689/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 7A–B</figureCitation>
); expansions indicated only by a tumid, black, densely punctured rim (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FBA81C0DFBE7F8C6" box="[1053,1145,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[154,1417,400,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-91@12.[154,1434,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia of G. stichtocephala sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500689/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface densely punctured with punctures of different sizes, concolorous to black, some on brown spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FBCD1C29FB4FF8A3" box="[1144,1233,1836,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[154,1417,400,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-91@12.[154,1434,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia of G. stichtocephala sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500689/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792159FFF4FF721C4AFDFCF86B" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22159FFF4FF721C4AFDFCF86B" blockId="11.[151,1437,1116,2043]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721C4AFED7F88E" bold="true" box="[199,329,1871,1898]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721C4AFEDCF88E" bold="true" box="[199,322,1871,1898]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Named for the punctured black rectangular mark on the head between ocelli. From the Greek. 
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF221C71FF7CF86A" box="[151,226,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Stiktos</emphasis>
(punctured) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712159FFF4FE171C71FD92F86A" box="[418,524,1908,1934]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Cephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FE171C71FD92F86A" box="[418,524,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Cephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(head).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792159FFF3FF721C9DFC93FEA6" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22159FFF4FF721C9DFB2FF81F" blockId="11.[151,1437,1116,2043]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721C9DFED7F856" bold="true" box="[199,329,1944,1970]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721C9DFEDCF856" bold="true" box="[199,322,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species probably has the same body color as 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712159FFF4FC351C9DFB86F856" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[896,1048,1944,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispina" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FC351C9DFB86F856" box="[896,1048,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">G. longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FBAA1C9DFBC9F856" bold="true" box="[1055,1111,1944,1970]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B2159FFF4FBAA1C9DFBC9F856" box="[1055,1111,1944,1970]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but all specimens examined are completely yellow. This species is also known only from males that have the ventral rim of pygophore extremely excavated. This species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712159FFF4FD871CE5FD54F81E" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[562,714,2016,2042]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispina" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FD871CE5FD54F81E" box="[562,714,2016,2042]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">G. longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FD671CE5FC97F81E" bold="true" box="[722,777,2016,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B2159FFF4FD671CE5FC97F81E" box="[722,777,2016,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the legs without large black spots.
</paragraph>
